goals.question: What is the overall trend of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?
goals.visualization: line chart of date vs. price
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the general direction of the S&P 500 index over the given time period.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the closing prices of the S&P 500 index?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of closing prices of the S&P 500 index and how frequently they occur.

goals.question: What is the average daily return of the S&P 500 index?
goals.visualization: line chart of date vs. daily return
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the average daily change in the S&P 500 index over the given time period.

goals.question: What is the correlation between the S&P 500 index and other economic indicators such as GDP or unemployment rate?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of price vs. economic indicator
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the relationship between the S&P 500 index and other economic indicators and how they affect each other.

goals.question: What is the volatility of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?
goals.visualization: line chart of date vs. volatility
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand how much the S&P 500 index fluctuates on a daily basis over the given time period.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["price"].median():0.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the closing prices of the S&P 500 index?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['daily_return'] = data['price'].pct_change()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='daily_return', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['daily_return'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['daily_return'].mean():.2f}")
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average daily return of the S&P 500 index?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
